CSS = Cascading Style Sheets, you can use css to style your web page. Use css with html.
Basically, without css your html web page will look blend with only a couples of block letter style and bold letters. CSS will change that in whatever way you can imagine.
* document is usually a text file structured using a markup language.
* presenting a document to a user means converting into a form usable by your audience.
* browsers is somwtimes called a user agent, which means a computer program that represents a person inside a computer system. browsers are the main type of user agent we think of when talking about css,
however it is not the only one. like you can convert html and css into pdf and print it out.


HTML is a the most common markup language but there're a couple more too such as SVG or XML.

 